text.tspan: Simply relaxing in the garden and watching the quiet lawn
mower doing the work? Or moving freely without cable
salad while trimming your hedge or drilling holes for
a shelf? Cordless, electric tools are in trend. Conversely,
combustion-powered tools are a thing of the past.
They are noisy and pollute. That’s why small gas-powered
equipment such as a lawn mowers or leaf blowers will
probably be banned in the near future. Instead, we can
see strong growth for green power tools equipped with
efficient brushless motors and lithium-ion batteries.
And what might surprise you: They offer the same or even
better performance.
This is due in particular to modern microelectronics. They
are part of the motor, the battery, and the charger,
where they help reduce energy consumption and increase
battery life.
